name: Dragon King by kaNO x KUSO
description:
"Designed as a tribute and homage to one of the biggest icons in American history, this piece was meant to capture the man's essence and attitude rather then being a carbon copy of his likeness. The Dragon King was a labor of love for me and I couldn't be happier with it; it's not often you get the opportunity to make a toy of one of your biggest heroes."  -kaNO

Designed by kaNO, produced by KusoVinyl. 

Limited to 250 pcs worldwide. 
Packaged in a gift box with flocked blister. 

Accessories: Baton and camera gun. 
Size: 8 inches

name: Kazuhiro Koguma by kaNO
description: Making a triumphant return in a new MPH exclusive colorway is Kazuhiro Koguma, the collaborative effort of Tokyoplastic, kaNO and MPHlabs. You’ll remember the tubby bear in the high tech chair from the award winning 3D animation company’s website who was brought to life by MPHLabs. This lounging Koguma baby is swappable with the other Koguma colorways to create new looks.

name: Street Fighter Mini Series 3-Inch
description:
Capcom's Street Fighter, now in its umpteenth iteration with over 29 million copies sold worldwide, teams up with Kidrobot to take you back to the arcade with the ones who kick-started it all - Ryu, Ken, Chun Li and, of course Blanka, the wild man.

All 12 of the original World Warriors, including the Psycho-Powered chase, are blind boxed and stylized in 3-inch vinyl. Gaming's best known fighters, each with their own unique fighting style, bring you back to your old pizzeria face-offs.

Figures feature articulated arms just itching to deliver that final sonic boom. 

This item is sold in individual blind boxes.

name: Family Guy Mini Series 3-Inch
description:
Kidrobot teams up with prolific animator Seth MacFarlane to bring you TV's all-American but totally twisted and dysfunctional family known as the Griffins, and their favorite New England neighbors.

Here to make us laugh and cry, each of the 15 blind-boxed Family Guy mini figures comes with an insert card and accessory - and raises the question, "Which FGKR will you get?" Giggity! 

This item is sold in individual blind boxes.

name: FatCap Series 3 Mini Series 3-Inch
description:
The wait is over.

FatCap Series 3 is here! Featuring 18 rad designs by artists new and old, Series 3 pushes the platform like never before. With a custom show feel, each member of the series reaches beyond the boundaries in graphics and sculpt, making FatCap crazier, hairier, cuter, meaner, and more human. Three mystery figures mean you really don't know what you will get... but rest assured, it will be epic. As individual styles, each FatCap is worth fighting for; as a set, they might be worth dying for. Save yourself the funeral fees and buy a case.

Artists who rock this series are: DEVIOUS, Flying Fortress, Jon Paul Kaiser, Julie West, KaNO, Kronk, MCA, Montana Colors, Pez, Queen Andrea, Quisp, Scribe, Shok-1, and Sket One.

This item is sold in individual blind boxes.

name: Intergalactic Android A/P's by kaNO
description:
The Intergalactic collectible is a take on the outfits worn by the Beastie Boys in their big hit titled “Intergalactic.”

Limited to 15 sets

name: HI-DEF by kaNO x ToyQube
description:
Hi-Def ONYX Edition

As kaNO's third figure following Moneygrip and Bodega, The NYCC Onyx HI-DEF steps it up with elegance and sophistication. Hi-DEF is 10 inches of fully articulated vinyl equipped with records and an M-65 jacket. Limited to only 100 pcs.

Hi-Def ALL WHITE Edition

In celebration of their 3rd year anniversary, Japan-based toy-store Tomenosuke released an exclusive all-White HI-DEF figure by kaNO! Limited to only 50 pcs.

name: BOOMBOT2 RASTA WOODGRAIN
description:
Respect in every aspect, mon.  The Rasta Woodgrain Boombot2 speaker pays homage the Rastafarian culture that promotes sharing of music amongst friends, family, and community. All Boombots are rechargeable, loud as &@*%, and portable enough to keep up with your lifestyle, guaranteed. Jah bless.

The wireless portable speaker fuses Japanese urban design with mobile audio in a truly portable package. The Boombot2 wirelessly connects via Bluetooth.

description:

name: KD x 123KLAN FEMME FATALE PURPLE RAGLAN
description:
Kweenz Destroy presents "Femme Fatale" a collabo with Montreal based duo SCIEN and KLOR of 123Klan.

Femme fatale literally means "fatal woman" in French, it can be defined as "the kind of woman men want...but shouldn't have!". Ever seen females who are seductive and alluring, yet clever, a bit evil, and mysterious? Like Poison Ivy or Cat Woman? Allure, mystery, and classy, dark glamour embody the femme fatale- but with a touch of playfulness of course!

Get cozy in this soft raglan pullover which features a loose fit that drapes against the body for a slimming look.

Made with Tri-Blend construction. (50% Polyester / 25% Cotton / 25% Rayon)

Model is wearing size Small in Purple.

name: TILT x KWEENZ DESTROY T-SHIRT
description:
Kweenz Destroy has teamed up with bubble letter master TILT to create this explosion of colorful bubble hautness. Features a 'Kweenz DestrHoy' (like today in spanish) bubble letters in the front and TILT signature on the back neckline. Crop it to your taste or wear it baggy style with some heels and ankle socks.
Ribbed collar. Made with 100% Cotton. Super soft jersey. Boyfriend fit.

Ribbed Collar. Made with 100% Cotton. Super soft jersey. Regular Fit.

name: Pink Pearl by Goorin Bros.
description: Pink Pearl is an a-crown fedora in a tonal pinstripe detailed with a bias cut triple pleate tie fabric band. This hat features a custom designed Peekaboo tipsticker by Amanda Lynn. The fabric is a combination of wool and polyester with a tie fabric lining. Catch a glimpse of your new lady friend as you flip over your Peekaboo collection hat and enjoy a special Amanda Lynn, hand drawn image of the girl of your dreams. You can start blushing now! Stay sharp with Pink Pearl. Wear it straight forward with a suit for a classic look or tilted to the side with dark jeans for a more modern feel.

name: Takashi by Goorin Bros.
description: Takashi is a high crown pinch front fedora in a tonal gray pinstripe woven detailed with subtle contrast button on the band. The fabric is a combination of wool and polyester with a cotton lining finished with a soft cotton twill sweatband. Ideal for closing a business deal, Takashi pairs perfectly with a grey suit for a classic look.

name: Hammond by Goorin Bros.
description: Hammond is a square crown flip up fedora with a contrasting double grosgrain band. This is a hat that will be in your collection for years to come. Available in three colors; black, khaki, and gray. The body of the hat is a combination of paper straw and polyester with a soft elastic sweatband.

name: Dude by Goorin Bros.
description: Dude is a sloped cadet in a stretch cotton rip-stop material. Sloped cadets have an extra seam that runs from next to the bill around the back of the hat. This extra seam gives a touch of softness to the sharp look of the classic cadet. Dude is the ideal everyday casual to add to your collection. The fabric is a combination of cotton and spandex, unlined, with a soft cotton twill sweatband.

name: Burbank by Goorin Bros.
description: Burbank is a cross paneled duckbill in our signature Burbank cut. The material is 100% cotton processed to have a slight sheen to the finish. Featuring an ultra soft twill lining to keep comfort at your highest priority, this hat is sure to become a wardrobe staple for all seasons and occasions. A Goorin classic.

name: PiiiiiG Bank
description:
Ever wish your coin bank can get bigger whenever you need them to? Or wish you could just take out a certain amount from the coin collection without the hassle of breaking the bank? Now here's a fun solution!

This PiiiiiG Bank comes with a cute style and an easy to withdraw/expand design. Simply open up the piggy bank and take out the coins as you need to. When there are more coins and you need more space, simply get another "PiiiiiG slice" (sold separately), and attach it to the body.

Feed your fortune to the pig and make him as big as possible!


Pig 5.3 x 4.1”
Slice 3.9 x 1.7”

name: Armed Notebooks
description:
Black notebook series with 3D covers of weaponry and unique pages inside.

Here, weapons which may typically be viewed as symbols of violence are converted to tools for peace. Our creativity and knowledge expressed through words and sketches are the best means to get our points across, not through force and/or violence - a strong message conveyed by the designer.

Grenade Cover: Extending the lines from the cover grenade, pages inside have identical light grey plaid patterns to make sketches and notes more organized. First page has a "1 Second" sign to remind us that time is ticking; use it efficiently.

Knife Cover: Every page inside has lines with slightly bigger spacing and blank bottom portion to allow different visual experiments with your imaginations.

Revolver Cover: No lines nor boxes on the pages of this notebook to limit your creativity. Use the wide space to figure out a plan in reaching your targets/dreams/goals in life.

Grenade: 5.1 x 7.1 x 0.55"
Knife: 5.1 x 9.6 x 0.55"
Revolver: 6.5 x 9 x 0.51"

name: Biddi Ring: Round
description:
Biddi Collection: "Virtual Leaf" 

Handmade rings by a local jewelry designer in Brooklyn, NY. 

The inspiration when making these rings was a thought of how sometimes we are like a "leaf floating down a river stream" in the virtual world of modern technology.  That is why copper leaves were used - and the cutouts in them represent our virtual lives in modern technology - imitating internal computer circuitry. 

The rings are a brass base metal and silver plated.  Inside there is a perforated and treated copper leaf.  In the color rings there is a base of colored mica powder from African rocks to create that reflectiveness. 

Adjustable size.
